// ----------------------------------------------------------------
//   DLLs can be loaded directly into PowerShell's memory using
//   [System.Reflection.Assembly]::Load(). This means:
//     - The DLL never touches disk
//     - No new process is created
//     - AppLocker .exe rules don't apply
//     - The shellcode runs inside powershell.exe
//
